'''Mohamed Attoumane''' (born September 9, 1981) is a Comorian swimmer, who specialized in sprint freestyle events.<ref>{{cite sports-reference|Mohamed Attoumane|https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/at/mohamed-attoumane-1.html|24 November 2012}}</ref> At age twenty-seven, Attoumane represented his nation at the [[2008 Summer Olympics]] in [[Beijing]]. He competed in the [[Swimming at the 2008 Summer Olympics – Men's 50 metre freestyle|men's 50 m freestyle]], and swam in the sixth heat of the competition, with a time of 29.63 seconds, finishing only in last place, and ninety-first in the overall standings.<ref>{{cite web|title=Men's 50m Freestyle – Heat 6 |url=http://www.2008.nbcolympics.com/swimming/resultsandschedules/rsc=SWM010900/index.html |publisher=NBC Olympics |accessdate=24 November 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120821063145/http://www.2008.nbcolympics.com/swimming/resultsandschedules/rsc%3DSWM010900/index.html |archivedate=21 August 2012 |df= }}</ref>
