{{Infobox football biography |name = Shamoy Thompson |image = |caption = |fullname = Shamoy T. Thompson |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|05|27|df=y}} |birth_place = British Virgin Islands |height = {{height|m=}} |currentclub = |clubnumber = |position = [[Midfielder]] |youthyears1 = 2013–2015 |youthclubs1 = Elmore Stoutt High School<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.virginislandsnewsonline.com/en/news/thompson-stays-cool-as-bfec-pay-the-penalty |title=Thompson stays cool as BFEC pay the penalty! |date=7 February 2013 |accessdate=27 March 2017 |work=Virgin Islands News Online 6}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bvisports.com/index.php/moresports/football/item/hat-tricks-highlight-bvifa-school-league-week-one |title=Hat tricks Highlight BVIFA School League week one |date=10 February 2015 |accessdate=27 March 2017 |work=BVI Sports}}</ref> |years1 = 2013–201? | clubs1 = Virgin Gorda Ballstars | caps1 = | goals1 = |years2 = 2016– | clubs2 = HBA Panthers | caps2 = | goals2 = |years3 = 2017– | clubs3 = [[One Love United]] | caps3 = | goals3 = 1 |nationalyears1 = 2012 |nationalteam1 = [[British Virgin Islands national under-17 football team|British Virgin Islands U17]] |nationalcaps1 = 3 |nationalgoals1 = 0 |nationalyears2 = 2014– |nationalteam2 = [[British Virgin Islands national football team|British Virgin Islands]] |nationalcaps2 = 2 |nationalgoals2 = 0 |pcupdate = 21:11, 27 March 2017 (UTC) |ntupdate = 21:11, 16 May 2017 (UTC) }}
'''Shamoy T. Thompson''' (born May 27, 1997) is a [[British Virgin Islands]] [[association footballer|football]] player who currently plays for the HBA Panthers and [[One Love United]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bvifootball.com/national-league-kicks-off-with-wins-for-sugar-boys-and-islanders/ |title=National League kicks off with wins for Sugar Boys and Islanders |date=8 March 2017 |accessdate=27 March 2017 |work=BVI Football}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bviplatinum.com/news.php?articleId=26358 |title=Competition Stiffens |date=20 January 2017 |accessdate=27 March 2017 |work=BVI Platinum}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bvifootball.com/leagues/mens-national-league/ |title=Top Scorers |accessdate=27 March 2017 |work=BVI Football}}</ref>
==International career== Thompson has represented BVI at under 17 and full international level. He was part of the under 17 side thrashed by [[Trinidad and Tobago national under-17 football team|Trinidad and Tobago]] 23-0 in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.trinidadexpress.com/sports/Cooper__T_T_taking_Suriname_seriously-163807426.html |title=Cooper: T&T taking Suriname seriously: Swamp BVI 23-0 |date=25 July 2012 |accessdate=27 March 2017 |work=Trinidad Daily Express}}</ref> He was called up in 2015 for a game against [[Antigua and Barbuda national football team|Antigua and Barbuda]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.virginislandsnewsonline.com/en/news/bvi-to-play-antigua-ahead-of-2018-wc-qualifiers |title=BVI to play Antigua ahead of 2018 WC Qualifiers |date=18 March 2015 |accessdate=27 March 2017 |work=Virgin Islands News Online 6}}</ref>
